The output integer represents the minimum number of moves required to convert all characters in `s` to 'O'.
The output integer is non-negative.
Additional requirements:
The method should handle the case when there are no 'X's in `s` and return 0 as the output.
The method should handle the case when all characters in `s` are already 'O' and return 0 as the output.
The method should handle the case when there are multiple possible ways to convert `s` to all 'O's and return the minimum number of moves.
